fix(browser_profiler): cross-platform 'q' to quit

This commit introduces platform-specific handling for the 'q' key press to quit the browser profiler, ensuring compatibility with both Windows and Unix-like systems. It also adds a check to see if the browser process has already exited, terminating the input listener if so.

- Implemented `msvcrt` for Windows to capture keyboard input without requiring a newline.
- Retained `termios`, `tty`, and `select` for Unix-like systems.
- Added a check for browser process termination to gracefully exit the input listener.
- Updated logger messages to use colored output for better user experience.

fix(browser_profiler): improve keyboard input handling

- fix handling of special keys in Windows msvcrt implementation
- Guard against UnicodeDecodeError from multi-byte key sequences
- Filter out non-printable characters and control sequences
- Add error handling to prevent coroutine crashes
- Add unit test to verify keyboard input handling

Key changes:
- Safe UTF-8 decoding with try/except for special keys
- Skip non-printable and multi-byte character sequences
- Add broad exception handling in keyboard listener

fix(dispatcher): enable true concurrency for fast-completing tasks in arun_many. REF: #560

  The MemoryAdaptiveDispatcher was processing tasks sequentially despite
  max_session_permit > 1 due to fetching only one task per event loop iteration.
  This particularly affected raw:// URLs which complete in microseconds.

  Changes:
  - Replace single task fetch with greedy slot filling using get_nowait()
  - Fill all available slots (up to max_session_permit) immediately
  - Break on empty queue instead of waiting with timeout

  This ensures proper parallelization for all task types, especially
  ultra-fast operations like raw HTML processing.

commits.message:
Adds certificate management script

Introduces a Bash script to automate certificate creation and management for Deadline 10 deployments.

This script simplifies the process of generating a CA, issuing server and client certificates, exporting PFX bundles, and importing the server certificate into AWS ACM. It also stores the ACM certificate ARN into SSM Parameter Store.

Excludes Deadline 10 scripts from Git tracking.

Prevents unintentional tracking of local Deadline 10 scripts,
which are not part of the project's core source code.

Adds private load balancer stack

Introduces a new CloudFormation stack for creating a private Application Load Balancer (ALB) for Deadline.

The private ALB facilitates internal communication and access to Deadline services within the VPC.
It also simplifies management of deadline certificates via SSM.

fix: Escape dots in release workflow tag patterns

The tag patterns were using unescaped dots which match any character
in regex. Changed to escaped dots (\.) to match literal dots only.
This ensures the workflow only triggers on semantic version tags
like 0.0.1 and not on other patterns.

commits.message:
feat(cli): add --version flag and improve version handling

Add a --version command-line flag to display the current version of iphone-framer. Improve version detection by using importlib.metadata, with a fallback to "dev" for development mode or older Python versions. Update pyproject.toml to version 1.1.2. Add .gitignore for image outputs and dist directory.

docs(agent): update AGENTS.md with v1.2.0 features, CLI, and development workflow

- Expand AGENTS.md to document new features in v1.2.0, including gradient backgrounds, improved frame rendering, and device support.
- Add detailed project structure, development commands, publishing workflow, and CLI usage.
- Document gradient presets, output formats, font system, and App Store compliance.
- Clarify file naming conventions and dependencies.
- Update architecture and processing pipeline sections for clarity and accuracy.
- Emphasize code formatting and cross-platform compatibility.

chore(build): update mise.toml for uv-based build/publish, add release/test-release tasks

- Switch build and publish tasks to use `uv` instead of pip/twine.
- Add clean-build, test-publish, version bumping, and release workflow tasks.
- Document environment variable setup for PyPI/TestPyPI authentication.

chore(release): bump version to 1.2.0 in pyproject.toml

- Prepare for release of new features and documentation improvements.

feat(cli): change default output extension to .jpg and bump version to 1.4.0

Update the CLI to use .jpg as the default output extension for framed screenshots instead of .png. Also, increment the project version to 1.4.0 in pyproject.toml.
